challenges here.

24
00:00:59,530 --> 00:01:03,460
We will only apply tools that we
already have, together with

25
00:01:03,460 --> 00:01:06,070
some new definitions
and terminology.

26
00:01:06,070 --> 00:01:09,560
However, this may be a good time
to review the different

27
00:01:09,560 --> 00:01:12,980
versions of the Bayes rule and
the examples covered in the

28
00:01:12,980 --> 00:01:15,850
